5000|$|Once {{the correct}} [...] "recipe" [...] of metal is available, the furnace is tapped and poured into ingot moulds, usually via a casting machine. The melt is then left to cool, stacked and sold on as cast silicon-aluminium ingot to various {{industries}} for re-use. Mainly, cast alloys like <b>ADC12,</b> LM2, AlSi132, LM24 etc. are produced. These secondary alloys ingots {{are used in}} die cast companies.|$|E

